commit.message: Implement return type inference for methods of builtin types.
Fix some return types. It is actually safe to infer 'str' in Py3 now.
Builtin types generally don't return None on slicing, and string types also never do it for indexing.
Do not only infer the type of a builtin method call but also set it as node type (if it comes out as a Python type).
Fix tests and adapt them to the new builtin type inference behaviour.

milestone.description: Remove support for Python 2 and Python < 3.8.
